Two men have been arrested  for allegedly tampering with a Transnet pipeline in the KwaZulu-Natal Midlands. Police spokesperson Lt Col Nqobile Gwala said police were conducting patrols on Curry's Post Road on Monday night when they noticed the men in a vehicle near the pipeline. “The  officers requested  backup and police officers from the Highway Patrol  and private security officers immediately responded. It was established that the suspects had tampered with the Transnet pipeline and a valve was forced open.” Gwala said the men, aged 31 and 33, were arrested for damaging and tampering with essential infrastructure. “The suspect's firearm and a vehicle  were seized. The suspects are appearing in the Howick magistrate's court today [Wednesday],” said Gwala. TimesLIVE